NAME
     range.place - interactive graphic tool for	range planning
     session.

SYNOPSIS
     range.place

DESCRIPTION
     range.place is an interactive and graphic version of the
     GRASS functions Gpat.place, Glos and  Gtraj.  Instead of the
     non-interactive and relatively cumbersome approach	of
     entering the parameters of	the function on	the command line,
     the user can step through the various parts of his	analysis
     using the mouse (or any available pointing	device)	to choose
     desired options from displayed menus of available choices.
     Menus will	pop down and roll up as	needed.

     The D language programs Dnew and Dchoose must be run in
     order to prepare a	window as the current graphics window for
     running this program.

     The user is presented with	a graphics window and, across the
     top, various options from which he	can choose: window,
     overlay, landpat, range, los, traj	and quit.  Most	choices
     made on the main menu will	route program control to another
     menu.  From there,	choices	will either display another menu
     or	execute	a command.  While executing different functions,
     the user is often given messages or prompted to type
     specific requested	information inside the "talk window".




RANGE PLACEMENT
     The following steps should	be used	to call	up and place a
     pattern on	the landscape using a base map as reference.

     1)	The user chooses a base	map to be shown	in the display
     window (which becomes the current window upon entering the
     program) using the	options

     overlay --> display --> perm/user --> basemap.

     2)	The user defines the pattern that has to be placed over
     the base map.  This is done with the menu choices

     landpat --> display --> add --> any_basic_pattern

     in	case of	a globally unregistered	pattern	or

     landpat --> display --> modify -->	land_pattern




