     7)	The user must specify the filename of the output grid
     cell overlay that will be produced	by the program.	 Upon
     choosing the option outmap, the user is prompted for a
     filename unique among overlays existing under the user's
     individual	mapset.

     8)	The execute option starts the program that generates an
     output map	on which the cells that	can be hit by a	shell are
     marked with integer values	that represent a measure of the
     muzzle firing angles required to hit the specific cells.

MISCELLANEOUS
     1)	The user can delete any	vector or cell overlay in his
     individual	mapset by activating the function overlay -->
     delete or landpat --> delete.

     2)	The contents of	the display window can be erased or
     refreshed by activating the functions window --> screen -->
     erase/refresh.

     3)	The characteristics of the database window can be altered
     after activating window --> database and then selecting the
     desired parameter to change from the sub-menu.  The user is
     prompted for the necessary	information.

